\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisian landmarks\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower, Notre-Dame Cathedral and the Louvre Museum are among the iconic buildings that will be on display in an event which is expected to last around three hours.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre-Dame Cathedral\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic buildings\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1016}, {\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"around three hours\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tour will begin at the Austerlitz Bridge next to the Jardin des Plantes (Botanical Gardens), while the L\\u00e9na Bridge, situated next to the Trocad\\u00e9ro Palace, will signify the end of the boat trip.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tour\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"the Austerlitz Bridge\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"the Jardin des Plantes\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"Botanical Gardens\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"the L\\u00e9na Bridge\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1218}, {\"ngram\": \"the Trocad\\u00e9ro Palace\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"the boat trip\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Austerlitz Bridge Jardin des Plantes (Botanical Gardens) Notre-Dame Cathedral Louvre Museum Eiffel Tower L\\u00e9na Bridge Trocad\\u00e9ro Palace Organisers hope to show that the Olympics is not off limits for anyone, in tune with theParis 2024slogan, \\\"Games Wide Open\\\".\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Botanical Gardens\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"limits\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"tune\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"Games Wide Open\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 600,000 people will be in attendance, with an estimated 1.5 billion viewers around the world watching the television broadcast, which starts at 6.30pm BST.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.19083661010519e-14, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Almost 600,000 people\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"attendance\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"an estimated 1.5 billion viewers\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"the television broadcast\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People who wished to be a part of the experience had the opportunity to apply for a free ticket from the 222,000 given out.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"the experience\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"a free ticket\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 100 boats will commence their journey at the Austerlitz Bridge and carry as many as 10,500 athletes along the city's main aquatic artery.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Almost 100 boats\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"their journey\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"the Austerlitz Bridge\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"as many as 10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's main aquatic artery\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Significant changes have been made to allow the river-based opening ceremony to take place, as the upper and lower quays running alongside the Seine - where spectators will be placed - have been closed to the general public during preparations.\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2144, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7045441559208918e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Significant changes\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"the river-based opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"the upper and lower quays\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2168}, {\"ngram\": \"the general public\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"preparations\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2244}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greater measures to ensure people's safety have been introduced in France's capital, with local authorities installing an anti-terrorism barrier along the riverbanks while also carrying out more security checks by searching residents and commuters.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9668130096518901, \"rank\": 0.03415991100131976, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Greater measures\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2263}, {\"ngram\": \"people's safety\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"local authorities\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"an anti-terrorism barrier\", \"from\": 2366, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"the riverbanks\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2412}, {\"ngram\": \"more security checks\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2457}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2480}, {\"ngram\": \"commuters\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boots on the ground have been increased, too, with around 2,000 private security staff and 45,000 police officers expected to patrol the city.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boots\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2502}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2516}, {\"ngram\": \"around 2,000 private security staff\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"45,000 police officers\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2638}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers will be deployed on top of buildings along the route, coupled with a cutting-edge anti-drone system to ensure that any terrorist threats are suppressed.\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2801, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Snipers\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2672}, {\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"the route\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2701}, {\"ngram\": \"a cutting-edge anti-drone system\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"any terrorist threats\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\":